
You are an expert full-stack engineer and product designer. Build a production-ready availability booking system with the following specifications:

Core Functionality

Create a live, interactive availability calendar web app that:
    1.    Syncs with Google Calendar in real time
    •    Google account: dmac.music.co@gmail.com
    •    Use the Google Calendar API with OAuth2 authentication
    •    Continuously reflect updates (near real-time sync or polling every 1–5 minutes)
    2.    Calendar Structure
    •    Display a rolling 60-day calendar view (grid layout)
    •    Include an option (toggle or button) to view/book dates further into the future
    •    Each day is a square in a clean, modern grid UI
    3.    Availability Logic
    •    If a day is marked free in Google Calendar:
    •    Display the square in green
    •    Label: “Available”
    •    Include a “Request Booking” button
    •    If a day is marked busy:
    •    Display the square in red
    •    Label: “Booked”
    •    No request button
    4.    Booking Request System
    •    When a client clicks “Request Booking”:
    •    Open a form modal with:
    •    Name
    •    Email
    •    Phone (optional)
    •    Event date (auto-filled)
    •    Notes / Event details (required)
    •    On submission:
    •    Send an email to: Derrick.mackey@lissiemarionshowproductions.com
    •    Include all form data clearly formatted
    •    Use Gmail SMTP or Gmail API
    •    Do NOT auto-confirm bookings—this is a request-only system
    5.    Client Distribution System
    •    Automatically send the calendar to 55+ clients individually (not group email) every 2 weeks
    •    Each email should:
    •    Contain a clean message
    •    Include a link to the live booking calendar
    •    Use a backend scheduler (cron job or serverless function)
    •    Ensure emails are sent simultaneously but individually (no CC/BCC visibility)
    6.    UI/UX Requirements
    •    Premium, modern design (similar to high-end booking platforms)
    •    Mobile responsive
    •    Fast loading
    •    Clear color contrast (green = available, red = booked)
    •    Smooth interactions (hover states, button animations)
    7.    Tech Stack (preferred but flexible)
    •    Frontend: React (Next.js preferred)
    •    Backend: Node.js (Express or serverless functions)
    •    Email: Gmail API or SMTP
    •    Hosting: Vercel, AWS, or similar
    •    Scheduler: cron (node-cron) or cloud scheduler
    8.    Security & Reliability
    •    Secure OAuth handling for Google Calendar
    •    Environment variables for API keys
    •    Rate limiting for form submissions
    •    Basic spam protection (captcha or honeypot)
    9.    Deliverables
    •    Full working code (frontend + backend)
    •    Clear setup instructions
    •    Google API setup guide
    •    Deployment instructions
    •    How to add/edit client email list
    •    How to adjust scheduling frequency
    10.    Bonus Features (if possible)

    •    Ability to manually block dates from within the app
    •    Admin dashboard to manage clients
    •    Email open tracking (optional)
    •    Custom branding (logo + business name)

⸻

