I found it! Look at April 25:

"summary":"Guardian Dental","start":"2026-04-25","end":"2026-04-26"
The Guardian Dental event on April 25 has an end date of April 26. Google Calendar all-day events work this way — the end date is actually the day after the event. So the system is correctly reading April 26 as busy because of that event.

The fix is to go into your Google Calendar and check the Guardian Dental event on April 25. It's likely set as a 2-day event by mistake. Open Google Calendar, find it, and change the end date to also be April 25.

Once you save it in Google Calendar, wait 2 minutes and your booking calendar will automatically update April 26 to green!

